When would you want to create a remote repository rather than keeping your work local?
When you are using multiple machine to work on, or if there are multiple people working on the project

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?
Fork is a copy of a repository that is created on GitHub.
Clones are copies of repositories on a local machine from eithera remote repository, or a local repository.
Branches are different versions of a repository, that may have different features on it.
